Atik BF16 Matmul/Attention Accelerator

This subtree contains the Atik accelerator design effort: a small RoCC-attached
BF16 matmul and online-attention accelerator intended to use a shared fixed-point
compute mesh, simple DMA, SRAM-backed tile buffers, and a minimal software ABI with PyTorch support.

Source files, design manifests, software ABI helpers, Benchmark (PyTorch) exporters,
Chipyard/RoCC integration glue, and documentation in this project are licensed
under the Apache License, Version 2.0. See LICENSE.

Atik builds on the Chipyard, Rocket Chip, and FireSim hardware/software
ecosystem and follows RoCC integration patterns common to Rocket Chip based
accelerators. Those upstream projects retain their own licenses and notices.

Historical Girdap design artifacts may remain only in git history or archival
branches; this branch is intended to be the clean Atik implementation base.
